snippet.textDisplay: I’m so sorry, Jeffree. 😢 I know this is so hard for you both. I think Nate is probably the best thing that ever happened for you, and you him. He is an amazing person and is so grounded. Having someone like that in your life and feeling unconditional love changed you for the better. I’ve seen the change in you over the years. Since you’ve been w/ Nate, you have become more grounded & conscientious, and far more confident, & as a result, more willing to open up and love without worrying about who loves you back. Being in the spotlight is insanely difficult. I don’t know how anyone does it. People can be so vicious and hateful (hurt people hurt other people). I think trying to be true to yourself through the years brought a lot of anger & resentment in your life b/c others in your life wouldn’t/couldn’t step up & do the same. I’m sure that left you feeling as if you were never “good enough” to be loved proudly & wholeheartedly. That’s SO SAD! But YOU were really the stronger one. And you have definitely been an example of resilience, willpower, and authenticity to self, and I admire the shit out of that!! Through this relationship, both of you have been an example of what it can look like to just love unconditionally & be authentic. You’ve inspired millions, in several ways. And now, you have a MUCH stronger emotional & spiritual foundation & a very different perspective. You’ve become a much more mature, conscientious & loving person, and I have thoroughly enjoyed watching you grow from that wounded person who felt they had to bite, scratch & kick anyone who wanted to get into the arena just to survive, to a person who knows that the world is a place for everyone, with all they have to bring to the table, & that all that fighting is just a waste of good energy that could be going into something positive. Now you can just BE YOU - wholeheartedly - and do what you love, knowing that you are here for a reason, you have purpose & are contributing something great. THAT is growth. THAT is good stuff. THAT is what makes the world a much better place! I think you’ve always been a leader; an old soul who was strong enough to choose a very difficult path and stay on it through the storms. I am sorry you are heartbroken right now, and I hope you do take some time to work through those things you didn’t give yourself time to grieve & properly process. But never, EVER think you are alone. It’s just not true. You may always be the the torch carrier who is meant to be out front, but there is never a moment that there isn’t someone there around you loving you and cheering you on. ❤️
